SIMPLE: pinner
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pinner
<hw>Pin"ner</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, pins or fastens, as with pins.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Costume)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A headdress like a
cap, with long lappets.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>An apron with a bib; a
pinafore.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>A cloth band for a gown.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With kerchief starched, and <qex>pinners</qex> clean.</q>
<rj><qau>Gay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A pin maker.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinner</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Pinner
<hw>Pin"ner</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pin</er> to pound.]</ety>
<def>One who pins or impounds cattle. See <er>Pin</er>, <pos>v.
t.</pos></def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pinnet</ent>⟦br⟧
